### Applications

#### Generator

A wire coil spinning in a magnetic field generates electricity.

This is equivalent to using an electric motor backwards, which is how most electric vehicles perform regenerative braking.

The rate of change of magnetic flux linkage is maximum when the coil is moving through the horizontal position - one side is cutting flux lines rapidly downwards while the other is cutting rapidly upwards.

As the coil moves through the vertical position, the rate of change of magnetic flux linkage is zero as the sides of the coil are moving parallel to the flux lines and not cutting them.

